<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcfc63fa5-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2129"><num value="2129">§ 2129.</num><heading> Ethics</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc63fa6-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2129/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Conflict of interest</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any ethics provision governing employees of the covered territory, all members and staff of the Oversight Board shall be subject to the Federal conflict of interest requirements described in <ref href="/us/usc/t18/s208">section 208 of title 18</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idcfc63fa7-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s2129/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Financial disclosure</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Notwithstanding any ethics provision governing employees of the covered territory, all members of the Oversight Board and staff designated by the Oversight Board shall be subject to disclosure of their financial interests, the contents of which shall conform to the same requirements set forth in <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s13104">section 13104 of title 5</ref>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idcfc63fa8-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/187/tI/s109">Pub. L. 114–187, title I, § 109</ref>, <date date="2016-06-30">June 30, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/563">130 Stat. 563</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/117/286/s4/c/45">Pub. L. 117–286, § 4(c)(45)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4359">136 Stat. 4359</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcfc63fa9-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idcfc63faa-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idcfc63fab-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/117/286">Pub. L. 117–286</ref> substituted “<ref href="/us/usc/t5/s13104">section 13104 of title 5</ref>.” for “section 102 of the Ethics in Government Act of 1978 (5 U.S.C. App.).”</p>
</note>
</notes>
